#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""lmswitch — list / toggle local LLMs from YAML configs.

  lmswitch init              bootstrap ai-models/ and symlink
  lmswitch                  interactive: list, then type numbers to toggle
  lmswitch list             print the table (read-only)
  lmswitch on  <name|#>     start a model
  lmswitch off <name|#>     stop a model
  lmswitch sync             regenerate opencode.json from serving models
  lmswitch add  <name>      create a new YAML config interactively
  lmswitch serve <name>     run a model in the foreground (for systemd)

Config lives in <lmswitch-dir>/ai-models/*.yaml. Models can be anywhere;
lmswitch init asks where. GGUF models run llama-server as a background
process; vLLM models run in Docker. Per-model `restart: on-failure` opts
into systemd-managed auto-restart.
"""

